BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The [`x`]-values in this table jump erratically. However, if we compute the rate of change between consecutive rows in the table, the result is always [$m]. For example, the rate of change between the first and second rows is

[```
                  \frac{[$y[1]]-[$y[0]]}{[$x[1]]-[$x[0]]}=\frac{[$ydiff]}{[$xdiff]}=[$m]
                \text{.}```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

